    <item>
      <title>Requirements</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/requirements/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/requirements/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;h2&gt;Minimum System Requirements&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;minimum-system-requirements&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#minimum-system-requirements&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;BIOS/CSM mode is not supported. Please ensure that your system is set to UEFI mode.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architecture:&lt;/strong&gt; x86_64-v2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Firmware:&lt;/strong&gt; UEFI (CSM Support must be disabled)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Processor (CPU):&lt;/strong&gt; Quad-core processor with a minimum clock speed of 2GHz&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Memory (RAM):&lt;/strong&gt; 4GB or more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Storage:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum of 40GB available space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Installer Requirements&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;installer-requirements&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#installer-requirements&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To successfully create a bootable USB drive for installing AerynOS, the following requirements must be met:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network:&lt;/strong&gt; An active internet connection is required for installation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;USB Flash Drive:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure you have a USB flash drive with at least 4GB of free space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-purple-200 hx:bg-purple-100 hx:text-purple-900 hx:dark:border-purple-200/30 hx:dark:bg-purple-900/30 hx:dark:text-purple-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 8v4m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;The process of flashing the ISO will completely erase all existing data on the drive.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-green-200 hx:bg-green-100 hx:text-green-900 hx:dark:border-green-200/30 hx:dark:bg-green-900/30 hx:dark:text-green-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;It is advisable to use a high-quality USB drive to avoid potential issues during the installation process.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Image Flashing Software:&lt;/strong&gt; Utilize one of the following recommended tools to flash the AerynOS ISO image onto the USB drive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;dd:&lt;/strong&gt; A command-line utility available on most Linux distributions for creating bootable USB drives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fedora Media Writer:&lt;/strong&gt; A reliable and user-friendly tool for creating bootable USB drives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rufus:&lt;/strong&gt; A widely-used utility that provides advanced options for creating bootable USB drives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Balena Etcher:&lt;/strong&gt; A simple and user-friendly tool for creating bootable USB drives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Hardware:&lt;/strong&gt; A physical keyboard, mouse, and monitor (or screen) are required to interact with the installation process. Ensure that all these peripherals are properly connected to the system before starting the installation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Downloading AerynOS</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/downloading/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/downloading/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;h2&gt;Downloading the ISO&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;downloading-the-iso&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#downloading-the-iso&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visit the &lt;a href=&#34;https://download.aerynos.com&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;AerynOS download page&lt;svg class=&#34;hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline&#34; height=&#34;1em&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
 &lt;path d=&#34;m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Look for the latest release available for download, the official ISO files are named &lt;code&gt;AerynOS-&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;desktop&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;architecture&amp;gt;.iso&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-green-200 hx:bg-green-100 hx:text-green-900 hx:dark:border-green-200/30 hx:dark:bg-green-900/30 hx:dark:text-green-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;There may be multiple versions available with different desktop environments denoted by &lt;code&gt;AerynOS-&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;desktop&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;architecture&amp;gt;.iso&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;desktop&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; is the desktop environment.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on the download link to start downloading the ISO file and associated checksums denoted by &lt;code&gt;AerynOS-&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;desktop&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;architecture&amp;gt;.iso.sha256sum&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once the download is complete, you can proceed with creating a bootable USB drive or burning the ISO to a DVD to install AerynOS on your machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Verifying the Checksums&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;verifying-the-checksums&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#verifying-the-checksums&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before creating a bootable USB drive or burning the ISO to a DVD, it&amp;rsquo;s important to verify the checksums to ensure the integrity of the downloaded ISO file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;Using the ISO file without verifying the checksums can lead to boot failures, installation issues, and potential security risks.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Linux&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;linux&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#linux&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open a terminal window and navigate to the directory where the ISO file is located along with the checksums.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~/Downloads&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the following command to verify the checksums:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sha256sum -c &amp;lt;checksum_file&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should see a message indicating that the checksums match if the ISO file is valid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;AerynOS-2025.03-GNOME-x86_64.iso: OK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the checksums do not match, download the ISO file again and repeat the verification process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Windows&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;windows&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#windows&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open a Command Prompt window and navigate to the directory where the ISO file is located along with the checksums.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; C:\Users\&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;username&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;\Downloads&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the following command to verify the checksums:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;certutil -hashfile aerynos-&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;version&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;.iso SHA256&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will give you the checksum of the file, compare this to the checksum found inside the checksum file.&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Creating the Live Environment</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/creating-the-live-environment/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/creating-the-live-environment/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;h2&gt;Creating a Bootable USB Drive&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;creating-a-bootable-usb-drive&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#creating-a-bootable-usb-drive&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;Creating a bootable USB drive will erase all data on the USB drive. Make sure to back up any important data before proceeding.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-purple-200 hx:bg-purple-100 hx:text-purple-900 hx:dark:border-purple-200/30 hx:dark:bg-purple-900/30 hx:dark:text-purple-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 8v4m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;Ensure the USB drive is properly ejected after flashing the ISO to avoid data corruption.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ll need your USB drive and the ISO file downloaded from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://download.AerynOS.com&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;AerynOS download page&lt;svg class=&#34;hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline&#34; height=&#34;1em&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
 &lt;path d=&#34;m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Linux&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;linux&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#linux&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insert your USB drive into an available USB port on your machine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open a terminal window and navigate to the directory where the ISO file is located.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~/Downloads&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify the device name of your USB drive by running the following command:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;lsblk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look for the device name of your USB drive, it will be something like &lt;code&gt;/dev/sdX&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;X&lt;/code&gt; is a letter representing the device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;Do not confuse this with the partition name, which will be something like &lt;code&gt;/dev/sdX1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Now run the following command to write the ISO file to the USB drive:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;Ensure you are using the correct device name for your USB drive to avoid data loss.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;This may take some time to complete depending on the size of the ISO file and the speed of your USB drive.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo dd &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;aerynos-&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;.iso &lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;of&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;/dev/sdX &lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;bs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;4M &lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;conv&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;fsync &lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;oflag&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;direct &lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;status&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;progress&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This command will write the ISO file to the USB drive and you&amp;rsquo;ll see a progress indicator as it completes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;5&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To ensure the write process has completed successfully, run the following command:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code&#34;&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo sync&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once the command has run, you can safely remove the USB drive from your machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Windows&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;windows&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#windows&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insert your USB drive into an available USB port on your machine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download and install &lt;a href=&#34;https://rufus.ie/&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Rufus&lt;svg class=&#34;hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline&#34; height=&#34;1em&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;
 &lt;path d=&#34;m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a free and open-source tool for creating bootable USB drives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TODO&lt;/strong&gt;: Add steps for using Rufus to create a bootable USB drive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Booting the Live Environment</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/booting-the-live-environment/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:45189/docs/users/getting-started/booting-the-live-environment/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;h2&gt;Booting from a USB Drive&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;booting-from-a-usb-drive&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#booting-from-a-usb-drive&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;Ensure that your system is set to boot from the USB drive. You may need to access the boot menu to select the USB drive as the boot device.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-amber-200 hx:bg-amber-100 hx:text-amber-900 hx:dark:border-amber-200/30 hx:dark:bg-amber-900/30 hx:dark:text-amber-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;Currently NVIDIA Drivers are not implemented by the live environment and will fallback to nouveau drivers.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insert the bootable USB drive into your system and boot from the USB drive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You should see the AerynOS boot process, and you will be presented with the live environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Testing the Live Environment&lt;span class=&#34;hx:absolute hx:-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;testing-the-live-environment&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#testing-the-live-environment&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2&#34;&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class=&#34;hx:inline-block hx:align-middle&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; d=&#34;M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0&#34;&gt;The live environment may run slower than the installed system due to the limitations of running from a USB drive.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once you have booted into the live environment, you can test AerynOS without installing it on your system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore the desktop environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test the pre-installed applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check the system performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify the hardware compatibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect to the internet and browse the web.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

